cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY. 

The paper focuses on developing a robust SLAM system for mobile robots in dynamic environments, which involves computer vision, machine learning, and robotics. Therefore, cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category. The paper proposes a semantic visual SLAM system that combines semantic segmentation network with moving consistency check method, which involves computer vision and machine learning techniques. Hence, cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also likely categories. The paper aims to improve the robots' understanding of the surroundings and accomplish advanced tasks, which involves artificial intelligence, and thus cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category. Finally, the paper deals with the integration of different components in the SLAM system, which involves system engineering, and thus cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also a possible category.
